message.content: We refer to Wikipedia articles on medicine for help. The history and physical examination findings suggest spondylolisthesis, which is a condition where a vertebra slips forward and out of place. The waddling gait and pain radiating down the leg suggest nerve compression, which is common in spondylolisthesis. Facet joint syndrome and disc herniation can cause back pain but generally do not result in a waddling gait or nerve compression symptoms. Overuse injury can also cause back pain but is less likely in this age group and does not explain the other symptoms.
